<paragraph id="79FB44676102B9875C373ED491475723" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">
<taxonomicName id="A4ABB15EADD369B3B853280C5C8AB485" authority="Melichar, 1903" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Udugama" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Udugama exoleta" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exoleta">Udugama exoleta</taxonomicName>
was described from Sri Lanka as the type species of 
<taxonomicName id="5435E8E3B20078D2C9B499CF59D42833" authority="Melichar, 1903" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Udugama" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Udugama" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Udugama</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="324B1C6F8D092429FA41A75A97B8EB3B" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">Melichar 1903</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="41E8DE4C6D19BFAE4BA3080A49F86669" author="Distant, WL" journalOrPublisher="Taylor &amp; Francis, London" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" title="The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhynchota Vol. III (Heteroptera-Homoptera)." year="1906">Distant (1906)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized this species name with 
<taxonomicName id="E45F77E8B1F99CE9DB90A192DC524E96" authority="Melichar, 1903" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Udugama" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Udugama splendens" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">Udugama splendens</taxonomicName>
described from Java, Indonesia. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="432EA4016A1DBF79A34EB9E65CE3BF42" author="Kirkaldy, GW" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique Bruxelles" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" pagination="9 - 14" title="Notes on some Sinhalese Rhynchota." volume="52" year="1908">Kirkaldy (1908)</bibRefCitation>
, probably based on comparisons of figures in 
<bibRefCitation id="FBE5ABCFA63DCBA0A732C3578179037F" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">Melichar (1903)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="ED4FECF5BE46B697F16CB2590B9906C0" author="Distant, WL" journalOrPublisher="Taylor &amp; Francis, London" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" title="The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhynchota Vol. III (Heteroptera-Homoptera)." year="1906">Distant (1906)</bibRefCitation>
, commented that 
<taxonomicName id="F74F99A9DBBB4E43F97EEADCA02CCF84" genus="U." lsidName="U. exoleta" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="exoleta">U. exoleta</taxonomicName>
was &quot;very different&quot; from 
<taxonomicName id="322DEFC7221BEE23933FD8BDA9BE6088" genus="U." lsidName="U. splendens" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="splendens">U. splendens</taxonomicName>
in having a much longer face. Nevertheless, the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4748FEE8F3295E4B4CA14BFB960CB12F" genus="U." lsidName="U. exoleta" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="exoleta">U. exoleta</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7927DFB4978DF43DD70CB9BDE6B106" genus="U." lsidName="U. splendens" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="splendens">U. splendens</taxonomicName>
was accepted by 
<bibRefCitation id="7B396D03DE450B032DF7416B0BB364AE" author="Melichar, L" journalOrPublisher="Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" pagination="1 - 221" title="Monographie der Dictyophorinen (Homoptera). Abhandlungen der K. K." volume="7" year="1912">Melichar (1912)</bibRefCitation>
, and later included in 
<bibRefCitation id="9BF8A4E111F7262326129B4D12B3B658" author="Metcalf, ZP" journalOrPublisher="Smith College, Northampton, USA" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" title="General catalogue of the Hemiptera, Fasci. IV. Fulgoroidea, Part 8 Dictyopharidae." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/aesa/40.3.544" year="1946">
<normalizedToken id="695A06EFEBEB3C25F795F16F5F4BB88E" originalValue="Metcalf’s">Metcalf's</normalizedToken>
(1946)
</bibRefCitation>
catalogue of world 
<taxonomicName id="877E318007D2FF3C459B45B0467AE055" family="Dictyopharidae" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="family">Dictyopharidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="115E8AA5EAE67D94B0CAABEC44D93BCC" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">
Based on our critical review of the published information and examination of 
<taxonomicName id="F9F136EAF5557B295C6DAD869A2E423E" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Orthopagus</taxonomicName>
material from Sri Lanka which agrees with the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="AAD1980B1F78786CFBF98ABEE474B18B" genus="U." lsidName="U. exoleta" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="exoleta">U. exoleta</taxonomicName>
, we propose here to resurrect 
<taxonomicName id="810DCEEA18E9F522199FFAED97D1FCC8" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus exoletus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exoletus">Orthopagus exoletus</taxonomicName>
comb. n. from the synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4D35F854FE5817C78710046D92DD910F" genus="O." lsidName="O. splendens" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="splendens">O. splendens</taxonomicName>
and to restore it as a valid species. 
<taxonomicName id="ECDFFE99A5F7C5575A746B5C9320B964" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus exoletus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exoletus">Orthopagus exoletus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="D2163CF0AE734B0058C3AD93487E25CD" genus="O." lsidName="O. splendens" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="splendens">O. splendens</taxonomicName>
by the coloration of the vertex and the structure of the male genitalia, particularly the structure of the endosomal processes of aedeagus, lobes of the phallobase and the shape of the segment X. The relative length of frons mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="3A6C97B94BA434422F4AB94F15BE203B" author="Kirkaldy, GW" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique Bruxelles" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" pagination="9 - 14" title="Notes on some Sinhalese Rhynchota." volume="52" year="1908">Kirkaldy (1908)</bibRefCitation>
is probably not a relevant diagnostic character because the length of the head in 
<taxonomicName id="E2A4115395970EBF76DE2AD91FCAAB81" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Orthopagus</taxonomicName>
species varies within a certain range.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="480B706D918392F94BB4D00853D80BD4" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="233C539F0F5603D88C388C7B102B0CC0" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">Melichar (1903)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="75015B282B7176DDBC54D403853639E4" genus="U." lsidName="U. exoleta" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="exoleta">U. exoleta</taxonomicName>
was described based on five female specimens from 
<normalizedToken id="7DE147CC43F48E04A247AC89E6D43A29" originalValue="“Moruwale”">&quot;Moruwale&quot;</normalizedToken>
, deposited in the collection of the museum in Colombo, Sri Lanka. This material was not available to our study. Nevertheless, we have studied one female from Sri Lanka, 
<normalizedToken id="C9C21F53D826647D1ADE7160E2A6421C" originalValue="“Puttalam”">&quot;Puttalam&quot;</normalizedToken>
preserved in 
<normalizedToken id="856FC67936CE045183E1401204C9B26E" originalValue="Melichar’s">Melichar's</normalizedToken>
personal collection in MMBC. Even though this specimen bears original identification labels handwritten by Melichar as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="748E0F4FEE8707B372EE65C7FDFB712C" authority="Melichar, 1903" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Udugama" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Udugama" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Udugama</taxonomicName>
&quot; and &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="1BD020B7F6653C50722A857B0F1B7009" genus="Fulgoromorpha" lsidName="Fulgoromorpha exoleta" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="exoleta">exoleta</taxonomicName>
det. Melichar&quot; and a dark red label 
<normalizedToken id="3AAA94B3C362F16EE0B5A9CF2B88614E" originalValue="“Typus”">&quot;Typus&quot;</normalizedToken>
originally also attached to the specimen by Melichar, it probably cannot be considered as a syntype because it differs in its locality and deposition from the information published in the original description and probably it was also collected later than the original species description had been published. Melichar did not use type labels in the modern sense. He had rather adopted the practice of placing a 
<normalizedToken id="827428D1121B9B63C557504F38FF1ABB" originalValue="ʻtypeʼ">ʻtypeʼ</normalizedToken>
label on one or more specimens of the most taxa (even on species previously described by other authors and identified by Melichar), specimens presumably which he himself used for comparison (
<bibRefCitation id="DDDA05A602420B576D3EA051B8018FC5" author="Young, DA" journalOrPublisher="Budapest" pageId="13" pageNumber="382" pagination="465 - 467" title="Types of Cicadellinae (Homoptera, Cicadellidae) in the Hungarian Natural History Museum. Annales historico-naturales Musei nationalis hungarici." volume="56" year="1964">
Young and 
<normalizedToken id="468B000C81ED23ED9814A2F26EA8B789" originalValue="Soós">Soos</normalizedToken>
1964
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DA94ABD462367F7BB817A71F3D723D71" author="Wilson, MR" journalOrPublisher="Brno" pageId="13" pageNumber="382" pagination="137 - 153" title="Tropiduchidae described by Leopold Melichar (Hemiptera, Fulgoromorpha). Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae biologicae." volume="92" year="2007">
Wilson and 
<normalizedToken id="B91BD8E28D6B547C61FA41A9F0226ED7" originalValue="Malenovský">Malenovsky</normalizedToken>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
